    {
      "name": "Saved Queries",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create Saved Query",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Employee List Query\",\n  \"description\": \"Lists all employees\",\n  \"datasourceId\": {{datasource_id}},\n  \"queryText\": \"SELECT * FROM EMPLOYEES\",\n  \"isPublic\": false,\n  \"isFavorite\": false\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/queries",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "queries"
              ]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "List All Saved Queries",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/queries",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "queries"
              ]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Execute Saved Query (Page 1)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"param1\": \"value1\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/queries/1/execute",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "queries",
                "1",
                "execute"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Execute a saved query and get the first page of results.\n\nResponse includes:\n- sessionKey: Use this to fetch subsequent pages\n- records: Array of result records (page 1)\n- metadata:\n  - recordCount: Records in this page\n  - totalFetched: Total records fetched so far\n  - hasMore: true if more pages available\n  - expiresAt: Session expiration time\n  - pageSize: Records per page (from user preferences)\n  - requestCount: Number of requests made\n\nOptional request body: Parameters for SQL substitution (e.g., {{param1}})"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Execute Saved Query (Next Page)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/queries/1/execute?sessionKey=YOUR_SESSION_KEY_HERE",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "queries",
                "1",
                "execute"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "sessionKey",
                  "value": "YOUR_SESSION_KEY_HERE",
                  "description": "Session key from previous response"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Fetch the next page of results using sessionKey from the previous response.\n\nHow to use:\n1. Execute query (Page 1) - get sessionKey from response\n2. Copy the sessionKey value\n3. Paste it in the sessionKey query parameter\n4. Execute this request to get page 2\n5. Use the new sessionKey from page 2 to get page 3, etc.\n\nSession expires after TTL (default 30 minutes, configurable in user preferences).\n\nResponse has same format:\n- sessionKey: New session key (or null if last page)\n- records: Next page of results\n- metadata: Updated with totalFetched, requestCount, hasMore"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get My Queries",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/queries/my",
              "host": [
